	     Harare - Zimbabwe's ruling
Zanu-PF party sacked President Robert Mugabe as party leader and appointed vice
president Emmerson Mnangagwa in his place, a BBC report says. The sacking of Mr
Mnangagwa had prompted an extraordinary chain of events as the military
intervened to block Mr Mugabe, 93, from installing his wife Grace in his place, the report said on Sunday. More to follow…   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  